<post author="Tim%20-%20Sprout" timestamp="Jul 28, 2012 11:12 AM">
<s>i'm with liam on this.</s><s> wow, how i wish i would have worked with this more before starting to buid this website on bc. do i start over and port my theme work to another package or do i grind my teeth on bc some more? 
</s><s>seo is key for a successful website and while i understand that meta desc and meta keywords are not the most important part of seo anymore they still matter.</s><s> i would probably say they don't make a difference anymore but just to be safe it doesn't hurt to have them setup correctly.</s><s> should google and other engines decide to use them in some way again in the future the site will be ready for it.</s><s> so why on earth would bc transition to v3 and leave meta tags in limbo?</s><s> not only is it in limbo but as liam points out - it causes issues with your html, maked duplicate tags, etc. 
</s><s>here is a simple implementation bc: 
1.</s><s> default meta desc and meta keywords somewhere in site settings.</s><s> if a page does not override them the default values are inserted. 
2.</s><s> each page has a seo section with page title, page desc and page keywords.</s><s> they override step 1 if supplied. 
3.</s><s> same for categories, same for products.</s><s> 
</s><s>why is this such a hassle when every other product out there makes this so darn easy?</s><s> ugggggh.</s><s> 

</s><s>now with my rant over, here is my hack to address this for now. 
1.</s><s> make sure your page templates have no meta tags (unless you want the same thing for every page, or you want to make a page template for every page). 
2.</s><s> add <meta name="description" content="your desc here" /> and <meta name="keywords" content="your keywords,go here,separated by a comma,but not a space"> to the page content via the wysiwyg on each page, bc will insert this into the head section. 
</s><s>not great but it's something.. 
</s></post>
</TEXT>
</DOC>


