<post author="Liam%20Dilley" timestamp="Dec 2, 2012 8:50 PM">
<s>this is a bit of a data dump but since someone did not renew the pre-release domain the site is down... Ê page seo metadata we are introducing aÊ new interface for editing page seo metadata by both partners and clients.</s><s> it can be activatedÊ by going to this url on your site:ÊÊ /adminconsole/#!/utilities/seosettings.aspx this will involve migrating some of existing metadataÊ from internal bc system into page content itself.</s><s> here are the effects of activating the new interface.</s><s> handling the following page metadata: description, title, robots noindex both of these can be set now when editing pages by using this dialog: changes: title, description and a new exclude from search fields will be also available in main view former page title field will be hidden (more notes below) ÊÊÊ search results will replace existing "exclude from search results" option.</s><s> if enabled, it wil place <meta name="robots" content="noindex"> inside the page. if existing content="nofollow"Ê exists, it will be preserved if content="noindex" exists, the selected choise will be "show", otherwise "hide" when a page is saved, if it contains the above meta, the following actions will also be performed: exclude page from bc's site search exclude page from sitemap.xml ÊÊ notes on handling page title page title can be set now both in html <title> tag (via the dialog above, dreamweaver or the code editor of your choice) (recommended), but also in the following field: when a page is rendered, it will use the title set in this field, if specified, and otherwise the value set in html <title> tag.</s><s> change: title will always be savedÊ in html <title> tag.</s><s> { tag_pagetitle } will continue to work in templates, and will render the value set in html <title> tag.</s><s> pages with metadata set with v2 interface this is no longer availableÊ in v3 ui.</s><s> please see above the recommened way to work with metadata going forward.</s><s> when new interface for page seo metadata is enabled, the metadata assgined with pages with v2 ui, if any, will no longer be rendered. Ê what is not being changed?</s><s> handling metadata for blogs, products or other modules. these will be addressed longer term handlingÊ facebook open graph or google plus tags per page these will not have dedicated uis, although we are considering it how about keywords metadata?</s><s> search engines do not use the keywords meta tag in web ranking.</s><s> if you'd still like to use keywords though, feel fre to edit the html content. Ê # migrating existing sites in order to activate the new ui, we will migrate existing data first.</s><s> 1. page titles for all pages which have the title set in this field we will move the title inside page content itself, using html <title> tag.</s><s> 2. exclude from search results page setting pages with exclude from search results set will have this added to page html code <meta name='robots' content='noindex'> 3. page metadata assigned with v2 interface for each metadata, we will move the contents in page contents.</s><s> example: this page <title>contact us</title> <meta name='description' content='contact abc company'> has the following metadata assigned description: contact xyz company robots: noindex after moving the data, the page will contain <title>contact us</title> <meta name='description' content='contact abc company'> <meta name='robots' content='noindex'> and have no metadata assigned in the v2 interface.
</s></post>
</TEXT>
